  "text": "We also proved that the highest expression of IL-33 mRNA was seen in inflamed tissues of UC patients in comparison to healthy participants and individuals with UC in remission. These data are supported by Kobori et al., [CITATION_1] Pastorelli et al. [CITATION_2] and Seidelin et al. [CITATION_3] The researchers confirmed that IL-33 mRNA expression was significantly increased in active lesions of UC patients. [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] In contrast to local overexpression of IL-33 mRNA in UC, a mature form (20-22 kDa) of the protein wasn't detectable in serum in all our groups. Nevertheless, several investigators have reported that serum IL-33 (20-22 kDa) levels were higher in IBD patients than in the control group. [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] Further studies should be carried out to elucidate the findings.",
